Our engineers average more than 20 years of experience in complex IT technologies and carry expert-level certifications. As a result, we have cultivated a global network of support services with unparalleled scalability and expertise.

Description: Bijoux Terner is a fashion accessories company that has been helping fashionistas all around the world look great for less since 1974.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Bijoux Terner is a fashion accessories company that has been helping fashionistas all around the world look great for less since 1974.  With our irresistible low price and incredible assortment of watches, earrings, necklaces, bracelets, pashminas, belts, scarves, bags, and so much, much more, you can always afford to keep up with the latest trends. And, with boutiques and merchandise in nearly one thousand locations in more than 60 countries across 6 continents around the world, you can find that perfect accessory in every corner of the globe. Bijoux Terner was born in 1974 from the mind of Salomon Terner in Miami, FL but the story really begins over a decade earlier. Terner, known affectionately as “Moni,” left his native Cuba in 1960 after the communist government nationalized his family’s business.In Cuba, Moni had been the president of the National Association for Handbag Manufacturers and, shortly after arriving in the United States, he launched a handbag manufacturing business of his own operating out of the basement of a local department store. From those humble beginnings, Moni soon found success designing handbags for airline flight attendants. By 1965, his young business was supplying handbags to more than 80 percent of airline carriers. Today, two of his handbags are on permanent display at the Smithsonian National Air and Space Museum in Washington, D.C.  In 1974, Moni founded Bijoux Terner. Originally opened strictly as a jeweler, the company soon began distributing custom designed jewelry at wholesale prices out of malls and merchandise marts. Before long, Bijoux Terner’s line expanded to include other fashion accessories. Moni’s daughter, Rosa, decided to follow her father and soon joined the company. With the two of them at the helm, Bijoux Terner enjoyed steady growth over the next 20 years. Then, came the idea that changed everything. In 1997, Moni and Rosa decided to try selling all of the jewelry and accessories at an underperforming kiosk in Miami International Airport at $10. The store sold the merchandise fives times faster than usual and, in just a few hours, sold out. Realizing that the simple price point was perfect for travel customers who were in a hurry, the company began targeting the travel retail industry with a simple price point strategy. Bijoux Terner boutiques sprouted up in airports, on cruise ships, casinos, and resorts all around the world. In less than a decade, the company grew to over 400 locations across 25 countries. In 2006, after thirty-two years at the helm, Moni sold the burgeoning company to an investment group.

Full Description: Sundance Institute is a non-profit organization that is focused on developing creative and financial support for the development of original stories for the screen and stage. It provides a space for independent artists to explore their stories free from commercial and political pressures. It is focused on developing documentaries, feature films, film music, short films, theatre productions, and more. It is also focused on developing its female filmmakers’ initiative, artist alumni, and artist awards. It is well known for its Sundance film festival that features films from around the world. It is also engaged in organizing educational programs, benefit events, and more. Its online platform provides its users with information related to its work and video clips, images, and overviews related to its area of focus. Sundance Institute was founded in 1981 by Robert Redford as an initiative to provide a platform for American film makers. It is currently recognized worldwide for its work and initiative. Sundance Institute is currently based in Los Angeles, California.
Industry Groups: Media and Entertainment, Other, Social Impact, Video

Description: Intellibot is a robotic process automation platform based on computer vision and visual programming.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Intellibot is an Artificial Intelligence (AI) company with end-to-end products and service offering designed for the modern business. With its proprietary AI-enabled Robotic Process Automation (RPA) platform, which incorporates many next-generation features such as machine learning, natural language processing, name entity extraction and computer vision, Intellibot simplifies the lifecycle of RPA deployment through a reliable, easy-to-use and extensible platform architecture. Intellibot enables organizations to create their own software robots, that are easily trainable, secure, flexible and reliable and can work on an enterprises’ day to day business processes, thus, becoming the digital workforce of the organization. Intellibot uses Natural Language Processing (NLP) to improve the efficiency of processes and positively impact the business. Its complex search capabilities eliminate ineffective results and its semantic search provides results that are exactly what the customers are looking for. It helps businesses implement natural language search on their own platform, and is compatible with multiple channels, including on-site, voice and chatbot. Intellibot’s entity extraction capability seeks to locate and classify elements in text into definitive categories thereby completely eliminating the need for any human intervention.   Intellibot is poised to make a disruptive entry through its AI offerings as its analytics expertise and quality of algorithms and data can scale across enterprise-wide information and knowledge needs.
Industry Groups: Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Hardware, Science and Engineering, Software
Founders: Alekh Barli, Kushang Moorthy, Srikanth Vemulapally

Description: Kar's Nuts is a food and beverage company in Madison Heights, Michigan.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Detroit Area, Great Lakes, Midwestern US
Full Description: Kar’s Nuts was founded in 1933, in a tiny kitchen in their home across the street from Tiger Stadium in Detroit. Here, Sue Kar roasted and sold peanuts to Tiger fans. The peanuts became so popular that a manufacturing plant was soon built to distribute peanuts to retailers throughout Metro Detroit. The company was sold to the Nicolay family in the 1960’s, and continues today as a family-run business. Still based in Michigan, Kar’s Nuts now roasts and packages nuts and trail mixes carried by convenience stores, grocery chains and club stores throughout America.

Full Description: Pharmacy Times is a clinically-based, monthly journal providing practical information pharmacists can use in their everyday practice. Each issue contains articles and features covering medication errors, drug interactions, patient education, pharmacy technology, disease state management, patient counseling, product news, pharmacy law, and specialty pharmacy. The Pharmacy Times Office of Continuing Professional Education (CPE) is accredited by the Accreditation Council for Pharmacy Education (ACPE) as a provider of continuing pharmacy education. Pharmacy Times is owned by Intellisphere, LLC, a leading provider of health care publishing, research, information, and education. Operating within both traditional and digital media channels, Intellisphere serves the needs of health care professionals through an extensive suite of magazines, journals, e-mail databases, Web sites, events, and personal meetings. With publications such as Pharmacy Times, Specialty Pharmacy Times, Oncology & Biotech News, OncologyLive, Contemporary Oncology, Urologists in Cancer Care, Oncology Nursing News, The American Journal of Managed Care, The American Journal of Pharmacy Benefits, Targeted Therapy News, The International Journal of Targeted Therapies in Cancer, and HCPlive.com as part of the publishing group, Intellisphere reaches more than half a million health care professional across nearly all segments of care.

Description: Leader in the development and marketing of products and minimally invasive treatment of venous diseases.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: The corporation VNUS Medical Technologies, founded in 1995, is the world leader in the development and marketing of products and minimally invasive treatment of venous diseases. The company currently markets the products of Closure System Patented system for patients suffering from symptoms associated with venous reflux. The Closure system began to be used in Europe in 1998 and has received marketing approval in the United States in March 1999. Description: CMP is a leading publisher of magazines and newspapers about technology, designed for the builders, the sellers or the users of technology.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: CMP is a leading publisher of magazines and newspapers about technology, designed for the builders, the sellers or the users of technology. The Company was founded in 1971 as CMP Publications, Inc., a New York corporation. On May 24, 1996, a new corporation, CMP Media Inc., was incorporated in Delaware. On May 31, 1996, CMP Publications, Inc. was merged with and into CMP Media Inc. so that, effective as of such merger, CMP Media Inc. possessed all the rights and became subject to all the liabilities of CMP Publications, Inc. Many of CMP's publications were the leaders in their respective market niches and five of CMP's publications were among the ten fastest-growing technology publications in the United States.  Of the three largest U.S. technology publishers, CMP is the only one which serves the broad spectrum of builders, sellers and users of technology and which is therefore able to offer technology advertisers access to customers in all three groups. In 1990 United Business Media, a UK-headquartered media firm bought CMP and did away with the CMP brand name, and separated the company into 4 smaller companies.

Description: Novatein Biosciences is a biological reagents company.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Novatein Biosciences is a firm that manufactures and distributes immunoassay kits, reagents, and proteins. They provide a variety of proteins and antibodies, as well as ELISA kits that have been verified. They work as a contract research organization (CRO) for their clients, supporting them with protein/antibody synthesis as well as immunoassay creation and setup. Their scientists troubleshoot several sorts of sandwich assays, including ELISAs, as a maker of ELISA kits. Their facility includes a BSL2 cabinet, CO2 incubator, shakers, incubator-shakers, ELISA plate washer, ELISA plate reader, protein spotter, array imager, FRET and alpha screen plate reader, qPCR cycler, gel documentation system, freezers, refrigerators, fume hoods, centrifuges, pH meter, western blot apparatus, PCR machine, FPLC/HPLC instrument, microscope, and other equipment. Our goal is to help expedite research and development by offering reagents and services.
